    {
      "id": "FGlglpuoX1zlxXHkxEIw5",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2397.154326034085,
      "y": 257.1919734577194,
      "width": 680.839599609375,
      "height": 1100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bWS",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1246682094,
      "version": 1018,
      "versionNonce": 1051383602,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782880317960,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Make system more scalable and avilable\n2. Reconciliation\n3. internal communication\n4. Integration with PSP\n5. Dist transaction\n6. Handling delays from PSP\n7. failed payments\n8. Security\n\n1. Make system more scalable and avilable\nInfra\nMulti region and AZ deployments\nEKS -> auto sclaing\nAdd redundency\n\nDB:\nAurora : postgres\nreplication \npartitioning\n\n2. Reconciliation\nPSPs send a settlement file.\nthat needs to be reconsilled with internal systems\ninitial balance + transactions = current balance ( ledger)\n\n3. intenal communication\noptions\nREST\nevents ( preferred) to decouple the system\n\n4. Integration with PSP\n1. Via webview or SDK ( FE integration)\n2. via API ( BE integration) : If compliance allows us to persist data\n\n5. Dist transcation\nSAGA : orchestrator and coreography\nwe go ahead with coreography\n\n6. handling delays\ndelays happen if risky transaction then we need manual review\nwe need OTP for debit card transactions\nwe show pending screen to users, till we get a confirmation\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Make system more scalable and avilable\n2. Reconciliation\n3. internal communication\n4. Integration with PSP\n5. Dist transaction\n6. Handling delays from PSP\n7. failed payments\n8. Security\n\n1. Make system more scalable and avilable\nInfra\nMulti region and AZ deployments\nEKS -> auto sclaing\nAdd redundency\n\nDB:\nAurora : postgres\nreplication \npartitioning\n\n2. Reconciliation\nPSPs send a settlement file.\nthat needs to be reconsilled with internal systems\ninitial balance + transactions = current balance ( ledger)\n\n3. intenal communication\noptions\nREST\nevents ( preferred) to decouple the system\n\n4. Integration with PSP\n1. Via webview or SDK ( FE integration)\n2. via API ( BE integration) : If compliance allows us to persist data\n\n5. Dist transcation\nSAGA : orchestrator and coreography\nwe go ahead with coreography\n\n6. handling delays\ndelays happen if risky transaction then we need manual review\nwe need OTP for debit card transactions\nwe show pending screen to users, till we get a confirmation\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Gb1QbCEJe_2OeLlTkfFRW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3104.856556761097,
      "y": 720.6629858563298,
      "width": 807.4193725585938,
      "height": 375,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bWT",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 373841326,
      "version": 629,
      "versionNonce": 845640754,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782881789396,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "8. security\n\nDDos : rate limiting\nEavedropping : HTTPS with mTLS protect data in transit\nMan in the middle attack : SSL with certificate pinning\ndata tempering : Encrytion protects data in DB, cache\nprivate keys are stored in HSM\nInstead, organizations use dedicated key management systems such as cloud KMS \nofferings or Hardware Security Modules (HSMs).\n\ncard theft : report fraud, otp, tokentization ( card -> tpken generated by PSP)\nAmazon stores token\nThere is no algorithm to recover the card from the token.\nadiitional security : step up auth, another factor of auth\nPCI DSS compliance : Payment card Industry data Security standard",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "8. security\n\nDDos : rate limiting\nEavedropping : HTTPS with mTLS protect data in transit\nMan in the middle attack : SSL with certificate pinning\ndata tempering : Encrytion protects data in DB, cache\nprivate keys are stored in HSM\nInstead, organizations use dedicated key management systems such as cloud KMS \nofferings or Hardware Security Modules (HSMs).\n\ncard theft : report fraud, otp, tokentization ( card -> tpken generated by PSP)\nAmazon stores token\nThere is no algorithm to recover the card from the token.\nadiitional security : step up auth, another factor of auth\nPCI DSS compliance : Payment card Industry data Security standard",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "3GoAeH4bMd-C0bpfbqHvB",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3135.820819042802,
      "y": 301.8468747982969,
      "width": 8,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
